    "updated_at": "2021-05-14T17:06:38Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I would propose that we could start issuing a warning for when someone uses an imported source which defines `pragma abicoder v1;` explicitly, while the outside is v2 (by default or explicitly).\r\n\r\nWe should have made this a warning with 0.8.0. It is not something which existed prior, as v1 was implicit and no explicit marking existed for it. I wonder if there is any legitimate use case where this scenario is required and is not done by mistake?",
